        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 23 at 7:13PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 712 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles west of Apple Springs, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Apple Springs and Centralia.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 100 AM CDT for
southeastern Texas.</instruction>
